<h2 id="answer_header">Answers</h2>
<ol id="answers">
 <li id="group_def"><span class="question">What&#39;s a discussion group?</span>A collection of <%= link_to "forums", '#forum_def' %> in which people at your school can have conversations online. A <%= link_to "group", '#groups' %> can be a class, all teachers, all staff members, or everyone at the school (to name a few examples).</li>
 <li id="forum_def"><span class="question">What&#39;s a forum?</span>A collection of related discussion <%= link_to "topics", '#topic_def' %> grouped together. A staff <%= link_to "discussion group", '#groups' %> could have a forum entitled "staff extracurricular duties", for instance.</li>
 <li id="topic_def"><span class="question">What&#39;s a topic? </span>A subject for discussion, such as, "Does anyone want to volunteer for lunch duty the week before Christmas?"</li>
 <li id="post_def"><span class="question">What&#39;s a post?</span>A reply to a topic, such as, "No".</li>
 <li id="groups"><span class="question">What discussion groups are there?</span>A discussion group is created automatically for every class, and other groups are created automatically for teachers, administrators, and the school in general. Different users can access different groups:
